Package com.esri.mo2.data.feat

Classes that represent the ESRI data model.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Cursor A Cursor is a collection of Data objects that can be accessed sequentially.
Data A Data is one unit of information that can be obtained from a Dataset.
DataID Implements an unique Data identifier that refers to a data source and an ID in that source.
DataListener Implements a DataListener and supporting methods.
Dataset Manages the retrieval of data from a local or remote data source.
Feature Implements a Feature which is a type of Row with one Field containing a geometric shape.
FeatureClass Implements a FeatureClass, which is a kind of Table Dataset that manages and retrieves one type of Feature Data from its datasource.
FeatureDataset Implements a FeatureDataset which is a type of GeoDataset that can have more than one FeatureClass.
Field Implements a Field and its supporting methods.
Fields Implements a collection of Field objects.
GeoDataset Manages the retrieval of Spatial data from a local or a remote data source.
Identifiable Implements an Identifiable Data with DataIDs that can be stored within a SelectionSet.
Lock Implements a Cache that can temporarily lock data to prevent deprecation during some significant operation, such as data retrieval.
MapData Implements a MapData object with supporting methods.
MapDataset Implements a MapDataset which is a kind of GeoDataset that can be displayed on a map.
QueryFilter Implements a QueryFilter which defines a non-spatial (attribute) condition for searching or selecting from a Searchable or Selectable Dataset.
Row Implements a Row which is a kind of Data that can be retrieved from a Table using the Table's search method.
Searchable Provides a search method to obtain Data in the form of a Cursor.
Selectable Provides methods that can be used to define a selected set of objects.
SelectionSet A logical collection of Row objects obtained from a particular Table.
Spatial Serves as a base class for Spatial data, that is Features and Images.
SpatialFilter Defines a spatial selection condition that can be added to a Query.
Table Implements a type of Dataset that consists of Rows.
Workspace Deprecated. - the interface has been deprecated, see Content API.
 

Class Summary
BaseCursor Provides a simple way to build a Cursor that uses a "peek" strategy.
BaseDataID Base implentation of the DataID interface.
BaseDataset This class is a partial implementation of a Dataset.
BaseFeature This class is a partial implementation of a Feature.
BaseFeatureClass A partial implementation of FeatureClass.
BaseField This class is a standard implementation of a Field.
BaseFields A standard implementation of the Fields interface.
BaseFilterCursor An abstract class used to provide wrapping functionality for subclasses that filter another cursor.
BaseGeoDataset This class is a standard implementation of GeoDataset.
BaseMapDataset This class is a partial implementation of MapDataset.
BaseMemoryFeatureClass Deprecated. As of MOJ 1.0, replaced by MemoryFeatureClass
BaseMemorySearchable Deprecated. As of MOJ 1.0, replaced by MemorySearchable
BaseMemorySelectable Deprecated. As of MOJ 1.0, replaced by MemorySelectable
BaseQueryFilter This class is the standard implementation of QueryFilter.
BaseQueryFilterCursor Creates a subset of an existing Cursor that must be filtered by a QueryFilter.
BaseRow This class is the standard implementation of Row.
BaseSelectionFilterCursor Creates a subset of an existing Cursor that must be filtered by a SelectionSet.
BaseSelectionSet This implementation of SelectionSet uses a java.util.TreeSet to store the ObjectIDs.
BaseSpatialFilter This class is a standard implementation of SpatialFilter.
BaseSpatialSearch This helper class supports spatial searching.
DataAdapter A standard implementation of DataListener.
DataEvent A MapDataset object sends this event to a DataListener when an error is detected during a MapDataset.search().
DataSelectionSet This class is suitable for small selection sets created from a Cursor, where the calling code needs to retain the Data after using the Cursor.
DatasetType Enumerates the kinds of Datasets that a Workspace can contain.
EmbeddedDataID This class stores the Data inside DataIDs.
SelectionCursor this class produces a Cursor by iterating thru a SelectionSet's DataIDs.
TransformationCursor This Cursor implementation is primarily used by the BaseFeatureLayer for drawing Features with on-the-fly coordinate system transformation.
 

Exception Summary
DataException A generic Exception thrown by class methods within the com.esri.mo2.data.feat package.
FieldNotFoundException This Exception is thrown by the Fields.findField method.
 

Package com.esri.mo2.data.feat Description

Classes that represent the ESRI data model. There are two inter-related models, one for Dataset and one for Data. Several helper classes are present for building implementations.
